CsvInfo

public CsvInfo(String delimiter,
               boolean headed,
               boolean trimming)
Instantiates a new CsvInfo.

Parameters:
delimiter - The delimiter to use for separating cells in a row.
headed - True if the CSV file has a header. A header is a row of cells that define what each column contains.
trimming - True if the values in the cells should be trimmed. Trimming removes all whitespace in a value.

CsvInfo

public CsvInfo(String delimiter,
               boolean headed,
               boolean trimming,
               boolean ignoreEmpty)
Instantiates a new CsvInfo.

Parameters:
delimiter - The delimiter to use for separating cells in a row.
headed - True if the CSV file has a header. A header is a row of cells that define what each column contains.
trimming - True if the values in the cells should be trimmed. Trimming removes all whitespace in a value.
ignoreEmpty - True if empty lines are to be ignored. If false empty lines will be added as empty rows to the resulting table.

CsvInfo

public CsvInfo(String delimiter,
               boolean headed,
               boolean trimming,
               boolean ignoreEmpty,
               boolean strict)
Instantiates a new CsvInfo.

Parameters:
delimiter - The delimiter to use for separating cells in a row.
headed - True if the CSV file has a header. A header is a row of cells that define what each column contains.
trimming - True if the values in the cells should be trimmed. Trimming removes all whitespace in a value.
ignoreEmpty - True if empty lines are to be ignored. If false empty lines will be added as empty rows to the resulting table.
strict - True if parsing should validate the number of columns in a row. When strict a valid CSV file has the same number of columns on every non-empty row.
